Requirements
1. Create a class called Pet

It should have these attributes below :

self.name = name (string)

self.animal_type = animal_type (string, like “cat”, “dog”)

slef.hunger = hunger (number starting from 50)

self.energy = energy (number starting from 50)

2. Add methods

def feed(self, amount)

decrease hunger by amount

if hunger goes below 0, set it to 0

print a message: "You fed <name>. Hunger is now <hunger>"

def play(self, minutes)

decrease energy by minutes * 2

increase hunger by minutes * 1

if energy goes below 0, set it to 0

print a message showing the new energy and hunger

def rest(self, hours)

increase energy by hours * 5

energy cannot go above 100

def status(self)

print the pet’s name, hunger, and energy

if hunger > 70 → print "⚠ <name> is very hungry!"

if energy < 20 → print "⚠ <name> is very tired!"
